Get Credit Risk Data - install packages

  • install & load all R packages
  • read the data
gitpath <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sureshlazaruspaul"
dirpath <- "/BUS662-practice-datasets/main/credit-risk/"

credit_risk <- fread(paste0(gitpath, dirpath, "crisk.csv"))

Create Plot Canvas

canvas <- credit_risk %>%
  ggplot(
    mapping = aes(
      x = loan_grade,
      y = loan_int_rate
    )
  ) +
  theme_tq_green() +
  labs(
    title = "Box plot", 
    subtitle = "Loan Grade (vs) Loan Interest",
    caption = "Data: Credit Risk dataset",
    x = "Loan Grade",
    y = "Loan Interest %"
  ); canvas

Show Plot Canvas

Creating the box plot

canvas + geom_boxplot()

Creating the box plot with options 1

canvas + geom_boxplot(na.rm = TRUE, outlier.color = "magenta", 
                                    outlier.size = 0.5,
                                    outlier.alpha = 0.1) -> boxplot1

Creating the box plot with options 2

boxplot1 + coord_flip() # flip x and y axis

Creating the box plot with options 3

boxplot1 + coord_flip() + facet_wrap(~credit_risk$loan_grade) # sep plots

Some animation using plotly

Creating an animated boxplot

canvas4 <- boxdat %>% ggplot(
    mapping = aes(
      x = cb_person_default_on_file, y = loan_int_rate,
      frame = loan_grade
    )) + theme_light() +
  labs(
    title = "Box plot", 
    subtitle = "Prior default (vs) Loan Interest Rate",
    caption = "Data: Credit Risk dataset",
    x = "Prior default", y = "Loan Interest Rate"
  )

boxplot5 <- canvas4 + geom_boxplot(); ggplotly(boxplot5)
